Merge branch 'master' of git://github.com/robey/kestrel
correct documentation for PersistentQueue#remove().
If requested, call writer.force() on the journal after any writes.

Add overloaded versions of the methods that Journal#roll() calls to
remove unnecessary syncing.

Add a parameter to Journal#write() indicating if FileChannel#force()
should be called before returning.  Other Journal methods that do no
additional writes to the journal can pass true; those that need to do
additional writes should pass false, thereby saving a sync.

Add a Configgy option to Journal if it should sync the journal after
all writes.
Make all the OverlaySetting fields val's instead of var's.

Make OverlaySetting's "local" field @volatile for the same reasons
that the var's in the PersistentQueue object are.  Also, make the
field private, there's no need for it to be public.

Fix a data loss window in Journal#roll().

Since Journal#roll() renames the existing journal and writes a new one
to the original path, if the JVM or system goes down while the new
journal is being written then it may not have all the entries that the
original journal does.  So write the new journal into a temporary path
and then rename it into the journal location.

Instead of building new File's every time one is needed, keep one in a
private val.  The JDK7 java.io.FileInputStream and
java.io.FileOutputStream constructors that take a String pass it to
the java.io.File constructor anyway, so this is saving a little amount
of work.

No need to declare QueueCollection's queueFolder constructor parameter
as a private val, constructor parameters are implicitly private val
already.  The only change this makes is it removes a private final
field for queueFolder in the generated QueueCollection.class.

No need to declare PersistentQueue's persistencePath constructor
parameter as a private val, constructor parameters are implicitly
private val already.  The only change this makes is it removes a
private final field for persistencePath in the generated
PersistentQueue.class.

Both the MacPorts git-core package and a standard build of git 1.6.3.x
provide git-rev-parse at ${prefix}/libexec/git-core/git-rev-parse
which is in a directory not normally in a person's PATH which results
in the "find-git-revision" ant target printing warnings.  So switch to
using "git rev-parse" instead.
Use a private val instead of a private var.
